<plot>Teresa Nguyen thinks about the same things most girls do in high school: independence, boys, college, prom, but she is anything but your average teen. Teresa has a moderate form of Osteogenesis Imperfecta, a disease that causes brittle bones. However, this debilitating disease does not define her. In this half hour documentary, Teresa's story will inspire and challenge you to view life from a completely new perspective.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?535759</url></doc>
